North_Little_Rock.Compton-Wood House: The Compton-Woods House is a historic house at 1305 S Spring St in Little Rock, Arkansas. It is a 2-1/2 story wood frame structure, with a cross-gable roof configuration, and wooden clapboard and shingle siding. It is a fine local example of late Queen Anne Victorian style, with a three-story square tower in the crook of an L, topped by a pyramidal roof.
